text: Max & Zhenya have spend three days at our place in Utrecht, which was much fun. I could tell them about my vision of the Netherlands as a foreigner, Menno shared local things as a typical Dutch. One day we have cycled together, it was very enjoyable time. These guys do quite a lot to diversify their life and to explore the world, even though they are both full time working people. Lovely couple!

Very nice and helpfull people easy to get along with. My wife and me felt most welcome at their modern home which interior design made us feel like we are in Europe. Sort of "little Europe" in Russia :-)
Higly recommended to stay with them or catch up when they request to crash your couch.

It was lovely staying with them. We met in the city and Max showed us around the city, recommended us the best places to see/visit, and even took us to a medieval festival. They were kind enough to offer us to stay one more night so we could organize our travel to the next city, and went above and beyond to organize our taxi and blablacar and make sure we were ok. We recommend them so much, you will have a great stay with Max and Evgeniia! We hope we stay in touch!! :)

Max is very nice and friendly host (unfortunately his wife Evgenia was absent and I didn‚Äôt see her). We had a lot of topics for conversation,  Max treated me by delicious food and theirs house is very artistic and cozy. Also cat Martin is really cute. Big thx for hosting and good luck in your future trip to Netherlands!

Ivan is very polite, clean and interesting. I host him 3 nights. We hanged out together, to the Tian'an men Sq and 798. We also talked a lot and I know the hitchhiking from him!
Hope you can finish you worldwide travel  Good luck to you, bro!

Ivan is a nice guy. He always has something to talk about and keep the conversation going. He is a good listener.

The first evening we went out to a restaurant to eat pizza with my English-speaking South African friend. Ivan was eager to practice his yet-survival-level English skills. The second day we hitchhiked to the Burabay national park and saw some exciting views, exploring thereabouts.

Later that day we returned to Kokshetau and Ivan assisted me in cooking a really nice pizza at my place. I called my friends and we had a really good time in the evening. My friends and Ivan hit it off straightaway, they liked him, and he liked them, so it was really cool.
 
Later that night my friends took us on their suv to the local hill with a view on the night town. Everyone was excited. It was all spontaneous. We made pictures.

In the morning of the third day he left for his next destination, Astana. I hope he'll find some good hosts on his way.

I recommend Ivan for hosting! Nice guy - we had interesting conversations. He respected house rules and was open to some remarks and advices. Was good to have him as a travel buddy for a short trip outside of Kazanüòä
Keep doing great and have good memorable travel stories!

text: Alexey is a very inspiring guy with an impressive experience in travelling around the world. My friend and I spent 2 days at his place and had interesting thought-provoking conversations. It's true that it's very easy to get along with him. His guide-skills are just great, we had a walk around the city centre visiting the most beautiful spots of Nizhny.

Staying with Alexey was simply awesome! Here's an authentic person with whom you get along pretty quick: after only a day, we acted like brother and sister, teasing eachother, having arguments and cool discussions, etc. Most importantely Alexey (we called him old man ;) ) has been on this incredible bike trip and has a tons of stories to tell and advice to give, and he is really good at sharing experiences :) He's also the one who initiated us to VK, now my friend and I are huge fans. He showed us everything intersting in the city and told us about its history (he will call them "boring stuff" but they re not) and taught us a lot about local food. We had such a great time when on the last night we cooked pelimini in a fancy way and we still cant believe how delicious it was :o
Thanks old guy see you on VK ;)
-The two so so small children

I had so much fun staying with Alexey! My stomach hurt from too much laughing (or was it from the delicious food that we cooked??). He picked us up at the metro, and brought us around the city. He knows a lot about the city and told us all about it while we were almost frozen by the Russian weather. Thanks to him we got the best look of nijni novgorod!. He took all his time to show us around and to tell us his incredible travelling stories. I hope that we meet again soon somewhere on the planet cause there's still so many stories you gotta tell us!

Alexey hosted me for 2 days in NiNo and showed me around the city. It was propably the worst weather to do it, but we still had a lot of fun. Whenever we passed a view point, he explained what's usually to see there behind the fog by saying "imagine this .... or imagina that ..." :D

After our time in NN, I drove with him to Kazan to meet with some of his friends and we continued our great time.
I was really sad when I had to leave, but I hope we'll meet again.

I love you man!

text:
Andrey spent a night at my house, and the next day we went to travel in the Golan Heights.
He is very pleasant, interesting, very nice and talkative. He has a lot of stories about his travels, and we had good conversations.  It was a great day together. 
Hope to see you again soon, Andrey!! :)

Andrey stayed only one night and about half the morning. He is very pleasant and interesting to talk to. He is also a very good listener and was very kind and helpful. I shall be glad to host him any time he wants.

It's not common that a guest makes me see some things in my home through his or hers own eyes but Andrey managed to so, and more than that, twice in the same evening. The first time was going to an observatory over the skyline of Tel-Aviv (which I have never visited) and second was an occasional rally. He also made me remember how special Israel is, having so many diverse landscapes over such a small piece of land. 
Andrey is extremely curious about the culture, society and life in the places he travels too seeking out some tourist highlights alongside unnoticed particularities, which makes his insights and questions so intriguing. We also had some fun time "diffusing virtual bombs" with a VR set.
Thanks for the time and the small souvenir. All Best back home and in your future travels :)

Fedor and his family are really welcoming, kind and caring. The typical *Russians are super hospitable* thing that I've heard about for so long, was reflected in the way they hosted and welcomed me in their house.
Another best thing about them is, Fedor and Svetlana - they both love travelling. This means, you'll get to hear many stories from them about their experiences. They shared many of their travelling experiences with me and really incited a spark in me to explore places that they have already been to!
Fedor and Svetlana, both helped me a lot with my itinerary. They guided me to a perfect plan to explore their beautiful city.
They also ensured that my stay was comfortable, and never let me feel as if I was from somewhere else.
Fedor, besides being so knowledgeable about travelling, is a great cook too. He kept checking on me everytime if I was hungry, and made me meals of my preferences! The best part - he cooks great too! :D
Their daughter - Christina is a great host as well. She's kind, sweet and really caring!
10/10. Would definitely stay again with them.
PS: If you guys ever visit India, do know that you've got a family there. :)

text: Taras is very passionate, independent and friendly person. He is interested in photography which became a common interest for us, so had a nice time discussing about several topics. I recommend him. Wish you good luck for your travel and studies, Taras. See you sometime. Cheers.

Taras and Julia are super nice and super friendly guys. I didn't meet them personally because of my stay in South Africa, but according to my roommates they are 200% reliable and trustworthy, talkative, sociable and respectful and thoughtful as well. These guys are great fun and awesome company. It was a great pleasure to host them and they will always be welcome at my place again.

Taras and Julia were a lot of fun to have over. We had a lot of interesting chats and had a real blast playing cards. Only too had I couldn't spend more time as I had to go abroad very early the next morning.

He and his sister are very knowledgeable and easy to talk to. At the house they are clean and followed the house rules. I can recommend them to everyone. I wish them the best.

Take care Taras!!
Glad to have had Taras and Julia over at our house for one night. I enjoyed the evening walk we did together. I found them to be social, curious and keen to learn new things.

I usually don't accept emergency request, but i have read Taras' profile and i have seen that he was quite friendly, has already some good advice being an host and liked hiking and the adventure. So I opened my door to him and his cousin Julia. 

Taras is someone very sensitive for the best and a little for the worst. He is very sympathetic, easy going, helpful. He is at the same time a bit rationalist, artist (musician) and sportive men. You could have a lot of good conversations with him sharing some biers. He like to understand others cultures. Despite his youth, he knows many references in old rock n roll and indie musics.  We had an intense connection by listening a song of the Doors. I regret to haven't had the opportunity to "fly away" with him a little more. But the destiny is like this. 

When he was at home, he followed the rules, was tidy, respectful, punctual, kept me informed of what is doing when he was outside. You can give him your keys without any problems.  With Julia, they cooked some russian foods that they bought although they didn't have a lot of money and that Taras doesn't like to cook. And at the end, he offered me a russian magnet.

I hope i will meet him in the future, see once again his joy of life, and perhaps be part of one of his hike. "Born to be wild". Have the opportunity to hear his "guitar gently sweeps". 

See you someday Taras. Keep the mood of the couchsurfer. But be careful sometimes : use protections. Continue to learn how to stay zen, open minded and kind in all situations, with everyone.
He came with his young sister in emergency couch, they were both lovely

I hosted Taras and Julia for 2 nights in Lyon, and that was a great experience. They are outgoing and friendly, young fresh and adventurous people. Taras is a very nice and smart guy, clean and respectful too.. I wholeheartedly recommend them

text: Only great words about Alexandr and his beautiful family!! They have been so welcoming, charming and warm that made my stay in Russia unforgettable! had the pleasure to visit their city home and their countryside home, spending the weekend in the forest sharing stories, food and building trampolines, boats and driving around in the fields (+ had the cool chance to try russian sauna and swimming in a cold lake)). He is very interesting and a great host; he will tell you he is a doctor but inside he is truly a world traveler ;) he has been to many different places. If you have the opportunity, you'll be lucky to meet him and his family. Wishing you all the best my friend, we hope to see you soon around the world!

I stayed with Alexander for a couple of nights. It was a unique experience, because  I met the youngest couchsurfer I ever met - this is Alexander's son Nikolai and he is two years old.

Alex and his wife Sveta are very, friendly, open and nice people. From the first minute, we began to communicate like the old friends.

They have a large family, a cozy and clean apartment and many fascinating stories.

I was very happy to meet Alexander and his family and it was very pleasant to stay with them.

Sasha and his family are simply wonderful! They invited me and my boyfriend to their life and we enjoyed it a lot. So interesting discussions, delicious food, funny moments and beautiful places. All these we had together. Wow!
Sasha offered to join them for a weekend and to go to dacha(nice house in the forest near the river and with russian banya). It was crazy experience!! Swimming at night in the river with fog after banya, watching football together. Super cool!))) I will never forget it. Thanks Sasha and Sveta) Greetings to your sweet children.
100% recommend!)

I met with alex close to his house and we went to the house from a friend to watch the game japon against to belgium, after we went to cook and eat in his house with his friend, and we had a good time speaking and watching the game. I like a lot his hospitality and so friendly, i recommend lodge with him.

text: Alexandr was a great host! Excellent location and flexible with our schedule. He is very accommodating and offers great advice for the city.  We had a great experience and would definitely recommend him to anyone. Thanks again!

We were amazed by Alexandr‚Äòs and Svetlana‚Äôs energy level as a family with three children. And they are very generous hosts! They took us on a sunset cruise on the majestic Wolga and Oka rivers and showed us around their city. Even after we had left their home, their tipps offered us great experiences for some further days on our journey. The restaurant? Delicious and authentic Russian cuisine! And the lake near Alexandr‚Äôs home town? Wonderful! You did not promise too much!

Alexandr is a very reliable and flexible host! He changed his plans so he was not there when we stayed in Nizhny but still allowed us to stay at his flat. It is located in  walking distance to the center and it was fun to sleep on a bed surrounded by unicorns and puppets ( he has two daughters and a Baby Boy ;) He organized his cousin and her lovely daughter to pick us up from the railway station. They stayed with us a night in Alexandrs flat, showed us around and called us a taxi for the next morning - without Lybas help impossible for us without speaking Russian! We had good conversations in the evening and enjoyed staying with them! Still we're really amazed that Alexandr let us stay at his flat without having met us before! Thank you so much!

I had the chance to spend a day in Alexandr's flat, I could met his very welcoming and dynamic family specially his wife who helped us a lot even if we arrived very early in the morning. Very joyful place that I truly enjoyed.

We stayed with Alexandr  and his friendly family four days. We had such a nice time and felt like at home. These guys are quite active, work a lot, but still they found some time to spend with us. Thank you so much! I really hope, that we can keep in touch, and I'm looking forward to hosting you, when you come to Basel one day:)

Alexandr is awesome host! He actually rescheduled his meeting in order to pick me at the train station at 7am! We have a nice chat with his sister over dinner and it's a shame I didnt get the chance to see his Salsa dance class as I have to leave the next day! Happy planning for your Asia trip and looking forward to seeing you again.

text:
Cherepanof is a very kind man, walks and extra mile to help you ! 
Was very kind to accept my last minute and followed up to check on me as well! 

As a host and as a guest I totally recommend him!

Sergey is a great man, he and his wife very graciously hosted me super last minute in Nizhny Novgorod in his self-described "spartan" home (they are in the process of building/remodeling). They welcomed me in even though they were hosting half a dozen motorcyclist friends (they are true motorcycle enthusiasts through to the bone) and fortunately they also are night owls as I was delayed with the Denmark vs Croatia game going to extra time and penalties. I immediately felt welcome and was offered a double helping of the tastiest, meatiest borscht of my life and vodka from some of his motorcycle buddies. They hosted me a 2nd night so that I had time to walk around NN, and made me feel at home throughout. I hope they will come to America and pass through Colorado on Interstate 70 on a great motorcycle road trip out west one day so that I can return the favor. Thank you again my friend and stay safe on the roads, cheers, Keith

Sergey and his family are really nice hosts. Very friendly and flexible (Sergey agreed to host me very last minute). They are nights owls so you can have an interesting conversation even at 1 am:-) Sergey is a biker and he has this kind of a free spirit of a biker in him that reminds you these old American road movies... In general: a very good experience.

It was a pleasure to be hosted by real motorbike riders. Wolle enjoyed to play with tools üîßüî®üî© together with Sergey and is happy about the small Voltmeter, a nice souvenir. We would¬† have liked to meet them again at the motorcycle meeting, but unfortunately it does not fit into our  travel schedule. Konni and Wolle, Germany / near Hamburg

text:
I met Karina, Sasha, and Rusland while they were in Kunming in the AFT house. It was my first time visiting a place like that, so I was very enthusiastic. Rusland describes it well in his profile, it is a place for autonomous travelers. They will not go with you visit a museum or a church nearby, nor will they organize your trip for you.

At the beginning I was a little disappointed because they were speaking all the time in Russian. I found that rather unfriendly. However, I couldn't have been more wrong. Later on this guys helped me a lot even though they were extremely busy organizing their moving to other city (thus their reason speaking Russian). My very special thanks to Sasha, who gave me a detailed explanation on how to leave the gigantic city of Kunming to hitchhike and to Karina who was very kind and also helped me a lot. These guys where honestly happy to help and share their experiences. Honest hospitality. 

Thank you a lot my friends, I will be sure to visit AFT again!

I met Ruslan on Phuket during my six month trip through Asia. Then we were on CS meeting and celebrating New Year together with friends. 
Ruslan is positive person with great ideas. We were talking about joining to buddhist monastery. I found him as a very interesting guy with positive attitude to live.
Ruslan is nice, honest,full of dream guy.i surfed his condo for one night,he let me use his condo by myself,and he moved into his friend's condo.

I have hosted Mikhail for 2 nights in Side. I was unable to show him around as I was too busy, but I can easily say that he is a good guest. Clean, polite, friendly and knowledgable. I strongly recommend him as a surfer and would love to meet again sometime somewhere.

Mikhail and Christine are very nice couple. They told us their much of their traveling experience, and we shared a lot about the economic and employment situations now in Russia and Italy. We are very happy we have hosted them. Also thank you for the gifts.
Him , his girlfriend and two of his friends stayed two nights at our place, they were very friendly to us and never made any problems at all. Very easygoing all of them.

I hosted Mikhail and his wife Kristina for one night in my boat. I am very happy to met them. They are very friendly, polite and thoughtful. 
If they want, you should accept their request.

Mikhail and kristina, you have a friend in  Turkey, you can call anytime you want. 
I hope we will meet again one day in a place in the world. Mag be in Russia.

I stayed with Mikhail just for two night ‚Äì but this time was enough to understand, that he and his wife are very positive and active guys, who have really enormous passion of travelling and wild nature.Especially I was enjoying our conversation about Kyrgyzstan, it was wonderful)))Also Mikhail treated me by perfect Turkish tee!!
Thanks for showing to me silver clouds, it was unusual for me, but interesting))))

Mikhail, if you'll be in Voronezh - I'll glad to see you again!

Mikhail was a very generous host. He dealt with us changing our arrival time to all crazy hours in the morning, and even stayed up to greet us. He took us to meet his friends and showed us some nice placed in Nizhny. He's a lot of fun to hang with, and I hope others get the chance at having the same experience.

I Just stayed with Mikhail for one night sleep at his house for one hour but he was so talktive And warm hearted.We walk around the nizhnynovgorod at night also his girl Friend is kind as well Thanks so much Mikhail I recommended him to every couchsurfer!

Mikhail and Kristina hosted me one night in Nizhny. We had some short and nice conversations. Kristina prepared dinner and warm tea for me, which were definitely life saver in a cold summer :) I wish you a pleasant trip in summer. If you need my help in any form, do not hesitate to contact me!

Mikhail and his wife Christina provided me with a last-minute couch while I travelled through Nizhny Novgorod. Even though our time together was rather short we had a good chat over some tea and chocolate about our lifes. They are a very nice couple! Thanks again for your great hospitality and all the best on your following adventures!

Initial plan was to stay for 1 night with Mikhail  but had to extend another due to personal reason. Mikhail was willing to help me plan a route for my day in Nizhny. Though it was a short stay and understandably due to his hectic work schedule, we did managed to squeeze in a quality time chatting about our travel experiences and there were several funny moments..Thanks for the comfort, warm reception and for sharing a glimpse of your Life.

My experience with Mikhail was great!! I arrived early in the morning at Nijni-Novgorod and he welcomed me in his house :D during the day we visited the city! He and Christina are so kind and talked with me in russian to let me improve :) i really had a nice time, very remmended!

Sonia and I thank you so much. We spent a really good time with Christina and you. The evening was funny and nice. And we enjoyed sharing the tea with you. Moreover Mikhail told us everything we had to see in Nijni Novgorod and he even went with us till the train station with his girlfriend.
We will keep an excellent memory of the stay.
Thank you
